ecanada.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/10-Skate-Canada-International.pdf |title= Skate Canada International |publisher= [[Skate Canada]] |date= September 2015 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160201050707/http://skatecanada.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/10-Skate-Canada-International.pdf |archivedate= February 1, 2016 |url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{Skate Canada International Figure skating}}\n\n[[Category:1988 in figure skating|Skate Canada International, 1988]]\n[[Category:Skate Canada International]]\n[[Category:1988 in Canadian sports]] \n[[Category:1988 in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition\n| title = 1988 Skate Canada International\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| comptype = \n| startdate = October 29\n| enddate = 31\n| skatingseason = 1988\u201389\n| location = [[Thunder Bay, Ontario]]\n| host = \n| venue = \n| prizemoney = \n| championmen = {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Kurt Browning]]\n| championladies = {{flagicon|URS}} [[Natalia Lebedeva]]\n| championpairs = {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Isabelle Brasseur]] / [[Lloyd Eisler]]\n| championdance = {{flagicon|URS}} [[Natalia Annenko]] / [[Genrikh Sretenski]]\n| previouscomp = [[1987 Skate Canada International]]\n| nextcomp = [[1989 Skate Canada International]]\n| previousgp = \n| nextgp = \n}}\n\nThe '''1988 [[Skate Canada International]]''' was held in [[Thunder Bay, Ontario]] on October 29\u201331.<ref name=SCRB/> Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]], and [[ice dancing]].\n\n==Results==\n===Men===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Name<ref name=SCRB/>\n! Nation\n|- bgcolor=\"gold\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''1'''\n| [[Kurt Browning]] || {{CAN}}\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''2'''\n| [[Viktor Petrenko]] || {{URS}}\n|- bgcolor=\"cc9966\"\n| align=\"center\" | '''3'''\n| [[Angelo D'Agostino]] || {{USA}}\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Matthew Hall (figure skater)|Matthew Hall]] || {{CAN}}\n|-\n! 5\n| [[Ca